{"_env":"NODEJS","_serializationMethod":"normal","_autosave":false,"_autosaveInterval":5000,"_collections":[{"name":"items","unindexedSortComparator":"js","defaultLokiOperatorPackage":"js","_dynamicViews":[],"uniqueNames":[],"transforms":{},"rangedIndexes":{},"_data":[{"slug":"about","title":"About","toc":[],"body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hi there."}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I'm a Canadian full-stack web developer living in Scotland. I work at an awesome digital agency called "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://www.primate.co.uk","rel":["nofollow","noopener","noreferrer"],"target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Primate"}]},{"type":"text","value":". I also take on freelance work that I find interesting."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I’m enthusiastic about normal web things, like intuitive experiences, blistering fast performance, accessibility, testing, and high ranking SEO."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I’m thrilled about newfangled web things, like Vim macros, easter-eggs, brutalist design, WebSockets, and experimental browser APIs."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"My favorite tools to work with currently are:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Ruby/Ruby on Rails"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Elixir/Phoenix"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Javascript (Vanilla, Vue, React, Stimulus)"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"HTML5"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"CSS/SASS"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I’m always looking to talk shop with anyone with any questions, ideas, or opinions. If you have any of these I hope that you "},{"type":"element","tag":"nuxt-link","props":{"to":"/contact"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"get in touch"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]}]},"text":"\n**Hi there.**\n\nI'm a Canadian full-stack web developer living in Scotland. I work at an awesome digital agency called [Primate](https://www.primate.co.uk). I also take on freelance work that I find interesting.\n\nI’m enthusiastic about normal web things, like intuitive experiences, blistering fast performance, accessibility, testing, and high ranking SEO.\n\nI’m thrilled about newfangled web things, like Vim macros, easter-eggs, brutalist design, WebSockets, and experimental browser APIs.\n\nMy favorite tools to work with currently are:\n\n-   Ruby/Ruby on Rails\n\n-   Elixir/Phoenix\n\n-   Javascript (Vanilla, Vue, React, Stimulus)\n\n-   HTML5\n\n-   CSS/SASS\n\nI’m always looking to talk shop with anyone with any questions, ideas, or opinions. If you have any of these I hope that you [get in touch](/contact).\n","dir":"/pages","path":"/pages/about","extension":".md","createdAt":"2021-02-26T22:11:49.038Z","updatedAt":"2021-02-14T22:01:24.307Z","meta":{"version":0,"revision":0,"created":1615222676434},"$loki":1},{"slug":"agency_work","position":1,"title":"Agency work","subtitle":"Ruby on Rails, Javascript","meta_description":"I build Ruby on Rails apps every day at Primate. Lots of them. I build and maintain robust applications that include event booking platforms, e-commerce, donation gateways, accreditation software, CRM integrations, and our custom CMS. I code well-tested backend systems in Ruby and turn our design team’s work into responsive webpages. We work with some cool clients so you should check out our website to see those.","link_text":"primate.co.uk","url":"https://primate.co.uk","published":true,"dir":"/work","path":"/work/agency_work","extension":".json5","createdAt":"2021-02-26T22:11:49.038Z","updatedAt":"2021-02-14T17:25:54.495Z","meta":{"version":0,"revision":0,"created":1615222676435},"$loki":2},{"slug":"boombox","position":5,"id":4,"title":"Cellarghost - music player","subtitle":"Vue, Javascript, Design","meta_description":"This is a webpage for browsing and listening to albums. I made it using my old band's music so had a way for us to host our records on our terms. I needed to take into consideration how different operating systems handle the Web Audio API as well as how different audio file-types across different devices. I also worked hard to ensure download sizes are as small as possible, whenever possible.","link_text":"lucylucylucy.netlify.app","url":"https://lucylucylucy.netlify.app","published":true,"dir":"/work","path":"/work/boombox","extension":".json5","createdAt":"2021-02-26T22:11:49.038Z","updatedAt":"2021-02-14T17:05:08.322Z","meta":{"version":0,"revision":0,"created":1615222676436},"$loki":3},{"slug":"dungeon_crawler","position":4,"id":5,"title":"CLI Dungeon Crawler","subtitle":"Elixir, Mix","meta_description":"I built this fantasy command-line dungeon crawler to escape the real-life doom of the pandemic. You choose whether to play as a wizard, knight, or rogue. You select rooms within the dungeon to explore in search of the one way out. You occaisionally enter into turn based combat with orcs, goblins, or ogres. Some rooms are littered with hidden traps and treasures. You win when you find the exit safely; you lose when an enemy depletes all of your health points. It’s coded in a functional paradigm using Elixir. You can play it by cloning the repo, installing Elixir, and running `mix run` in your command line.","published":true,"link_text":"github.com/cfbonner/dungeon_crawler","url":"https://github.com/cfbonner/dungeon_crawler","dir":"/work","path":"/work/dungeon_crawler","extension":".json5","createdAt":"2021-02-26T22:11:49.038Z","updatedAt":"2021-02-14T21:11:02.697Z","meta":{"version":0,"revision":0,"created":1615222676437},"$loki":4},{"slug":"flourish_festival","id":2,"position":2,"title":"FLOURISH Festival","subtitle":"Ruby on Rails, Javascript, Design","meta_description":"This is a site for a grassroots Canadian music and art festival. It leverages ActiveAdmin for managing yearly iterations of the festival. The site is used to publish lineups, schedules, trailers, and a 3D rendered map of the town's participating venues. It is also used to collect artist submissions, sell tickets, and send emails. Under this cute/colorful exterior is a pretty powerful website.","link_text":"flourish-fest.com","url":"https://www.flourish-fest.com","published":true,"dir":"/work","path":"/work/flourish_festival","extension":".json5","createdAt":"2021-03-08T16:57:20.427Z","updatedAt":"2021-03-08T16:57:20.427Z","meta":{"version":0,"revision":0,"created":1615222676438},"$loki":5},{"slug":"lofter","position":3,"id":7,"title":"Lofter","subtitle":"Elixir, Phoenix, LiveView","meta_description":"There's a free pitch-and-putt golf course near my house in Edinburgh. I made this LiveView application so that I could keep track of my games on the links. Users share scorecards over a web-socket connection and can watch each other’s scores update in real-time. Sadly, this has not helped me become any better at golf.","link_text":"lofter.herokuapp.com","url":"https://lofter.herokuapp.com","published":true,"dir":"/work","path":"/work/lofter","extension":".json5","createdAt":"2021-02-26T22:11:49.038Z","updatedAt":"2021-02-15T18:01:09.964Z","meta":{"version":0,"revision":0,"created":1615222676438},"$loki":6},{"slug":"log_lady","id":6,"title":"Log Lady Ipsum","subtitle":"Phoenix, Javascript","meta_description":"Graciously serves up Twin Peaks' Log Lady monologues from an API written in Elixir/Phoenix and consumed in a Nuxt.js app. I need placeholder text quite often in my line of work, and I love Twin Peaks so this was pretty necessary after the site I used to use (damngoodcoffeeipsum.com I think?) went offline.","link_text":"logladyipsum.netlify.app","url":"https://logladyipsum.netlify.app/","published":false,"dir":"/work","path":"/work/log_lady","extension":".json5","createdAt":"2021-02-26T22:11:49.038Z","updatedAt":"2021-02-14T12:02:02.763Z","meta":{"version":0,"revision":0,"created":1615222676439},"$loki":7},{"slug":"tattler","position":6,"id":3,"title":"Tattler - Chat app","subtitle":"Phoenix, Javascript","meta_description":"My take on a classic Elixir/Phoenix app. You can generate a chatroom at any `/chat` endpoint, send the link to some safe internet friends, and chat away.","link_text":"tattlr.herokuapp.com","url":"https://tattlr.herokuapp.com/","published":true,"dir":"/work","path":"/work/tattler","extension":".json5","createdAt":"2021-02-26T22:11:49.038Z","updatedAt":"2021-02-14T17:05:23.530Z","meta":{"version":0,"revision":0,"created":1615222676440},"$loki":8}],"idIndex":[1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8],"maxId":8,"_dirty":true,"_nestedProperties":[],"transactio